{"questionId":"22671118","questionHtml":"<p>By substituting into the original model, show that, for small values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi></math>:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>X</mi><mo>.</mo></mover><mo>≈</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>Y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to substitute&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>Y</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Y</mi></math>&nbsp; into&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M</strong></em><em><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>X</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>X</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>Y</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>X</mi><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>X</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>X</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>Y</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>X</mi><mi>Y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>Y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>X</mi><mi>Y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong></em><em><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>The term in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>X</mi><mi>Y</mi></math> can be ignored.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R</strong></em><em><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>Y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mo>⋯</mo><mo>≈</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>Y</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through can be awarded for the <em><strong>M1</strong></em> and <strong><em>R1</em></strong> but not the <em><strong>A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22671118","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ2.2e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"By substituting into the original model, show that, for small values of X and Y: X.≈-3Y2.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}